Trim the @Pak Choi{1} then thinly slice widthways. Halve the @mangetout{80%g} lengthways. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}.

Pour the cold @water{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting lid. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp}, cover with the #lid{} and bring to the boil on medium-high heat. Once boiling, turn the heat down to its lowest setting. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the #pan{} from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Drain and discard any excess fat from the beef, then season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the mince is browned, lower the heat then add the bok choy. Cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Next add the garlic, @Thai style spice mix{1} and @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Add the @water{100%ml}. Add the mangetout then stir everything together well. Simmer, stirring frequently until the liquid has reduced by half and the mangetout are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> Be careful, the Thai spice is spicy - add less if you don't like heat.

When the beef is ready, stir through the @hoisin sauce{64%g} and @honey{15%g}, add a squeeze of lime juice. Remove from the heat, taste and season with @salt{}, @black pepper{} and @?sugar{} if necessary. Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest. Get ready to serve.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Share the rice between your #bowls{} and serve the hoisin beef on top. Chop the remaining lime into wedges and serve alongside for anyone who likes things extra zesty. Enjoy!